Package application

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    CreateController
    The CreateController class, represents the Create new recipe view, and connects UI with back end and implements EventHandler to get action events from JavaFX and Initializable to switch scenes and update certain models.
    EditorController
    The EditorController class, represents the Edit existing recipe view, and connects UI with back end and implements EventHandler to get action events from JavaFX and Initializable to switch scenes and update certain models.
    Home_BrowseController
    The Home_BrowseController class, represents the Home View after data is loaded, and connects UI with back end and implements EventHandler to get action events from JavaFX and Initializable to switch scenes and update certain models.
    Ingredient
    Ingredient is a Java class representing an Ingredient object with a name, amount, unit of measurement, and number of calories.
    Main
    The Main class contains the main method to run the program and creates the UI, as well as the storage data files the program will use, then will switch scenes.
    Recipe
    CardModel is a Java class representing a RecipeObject with a name, number of servings number of total calories, list of ingredients, and list of tags.
    SearchController
    The Search class, represents the recipe Search View, and connects UI with back end and implements EventHandler to get action events from JavaFX and Initializable to switch scenes and update certain models.
    ViewController
    The View class, represents the recipe Viewer View, and connects UI with back end and implements EventHandler to get action events from JavaFX and Initializable to switch scenes and update certain models.
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    EUnitType
    The EUnitType class represents every measurement type you'd use while cooking.
